author: Roberto Gimoro
notes: Bisakol is the dialect spoken by the people of Bulan, Matnog, Irosin, Bulusan, Gubat, Sta Magdalena and other adjacent towns of the province of Sorsogon, Bikol Region.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Philippine, Greater Central Philippine, Central Philippine, Bikol, Coastal, Naga
